            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-12-16 12:19:05" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>(diminutive of {L:παῖς&lt;SDBG:παῖς:000001&gt;}[b] ‘child,’ {D:10.36}, but with the loss of at least most of the diminutive meaning) one’s immediate offspring</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>child</Gloss>
                <Gloss>offspring</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>One need not assume in {S:04201100700030} that the children were in the same bed with their father. One may render this passage simply as ‘I have gone to bed and so have my children’ or ‘I am already in bed and so are my children,’ but see {D:6.108}.</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
